   A man convicted of trying to smuggle
foreign currency was sentenced to death Sunday by a military court.
   Sudan Airways pilot Girgis Butrus, who will be hanged, was
convicted Saturday by the special military tribunal of trying to
smuggle more than $100,000 worth of foreign currency out of Sudan.
   The court said he was guilty of ``subversion of the Sudanese
