<FIRST>u a AM-ExxonExplosion     12-24 0102</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Exxon Explosion,0105</SECOND>
<HEAD>Blast Rocks Refinery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A powerful explosion rocked the storage
tank area of an Exxon refinery Sunday.
   No injuries were immediately reported, but the explosion touched
off a roaring fire and sent a plume of smoke 500 feet in the air,
said East Baton Rouge Civil Defense spokesman Ed Wright.
   The tank storage area is near a pipeline, Wright said.
   The blast shattered windows in the surrounding area and the
concussion could be felt as far away as 15 miles, residents said.
   A brief power outage was reported immediately after the
explosion, Wright said.
</TEXT>
